  "doc_id": "51097",
  "text": "Interestingly, the morphology of T3-DO in the metathoracic ganglion as well as its descending axon with projections in every unfused abdominal ganglion resembles the ventilation-coordinating interneurons identified in locusts [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Considering that in a singing cricket, the abdominal ventilation cycles are strictly coupled to the chirp rhythm [CITATION_3] , the axonal projections of T3-DO in the posterior abdominal ganglia could link the singing CPG output to the abdominal ventilatory oscillators [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
